## Burn the bridge. {#burn-the-bridge-dot}

Instead of keeping spacemacs and classical Emacs I have decided to burn the bridge by deleting the spacemacs configuration directory. (off-course I have the backup kept somewhere safe)


## Starting Fresh {#starting-fresh}


### Default basic setup {#default-basic-setup}

Deleting the spacemacs Emacs.d file and restarting the Emacs started the vanilla Emacs. As a noob on vanilla Emacs I will be using customization instead of solely depend on text configuration.


### Startup configuration {#startup-configuration}

{{< highlight org >}}
(setq initial-scratch-message nil)
(tool-bar-mode -1)
(menu-bar-mode -1)
(toggle-scroll-bar -1)
{{< /highlight >}}


### Package managers {#package-managers}

{{< highlight lisp >}}
(require 'package)
(setq package-archives '(("melpa" . "https://melpa.org/packages/")
			 ("org" . "https://orgmode.org/elpa/")
			 ("elpa" . "https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/")))
{{< /highlight >}}


### Evil mode {#evil-mode}

One of the important reason for spacemacs was evil mode. Hence first thing was to enable it after

{{< highlight lisp >}}
(require 'evil)
(evil-mode 1)
{{< /highlight >}}

How can Evil complete without mapping emacs exit current operation command by Escape key.

{{< highlight lisp >}}
(global-set-key (kbd "<escape>") 'keyboard-escape-quit)
{{< /highlight >}}


### Line Numbers {#line-numbers}

{{< highlight lisp >}}
(global-display-line-numbers-mode 1)
{{< /highlight >}}


### Recent files (Vim Startify) {#recent-files--vim-startify}

{{< highlight lisp >}}
(recentf-mode 1)
(setq recentf-max-menu-items 25)
(setq recentf-max-saved-items 25)
(global-set-key "\C-x\ \C-r" 'recentf-open-files)
{{< /highlight >}}


### Org Mode {#org-mode}


#### Agenda {#agenda}

Created a file in home directory and added to agenda list using "C-c ["


### Completion {#completion}

[Thanks to SystemCrafter](https://systemcrafters.net/emacs-tips/streamline-completions-with-vertico/) I am using vertico


### Which key {#which-key}

This mode give nice options of displaying options of next command.

{{< highlight eli >}}
(which-key-mode)
{{< /highlight >}}


### Programming Literate Programming {#programming-literate-programming}

{{< highlight org >}}
'org-babel-load-languages
'((python . t)))
{{< /highlight >}}

(org-babel-do-load-languages

